  "text": "Endothelial-dependent dysfunction is another pathway that may be implicated in the pathogenesis of AF. Occurrence of AF in myocardial infarction was associated with circulating markers of endothelial dysfunction and oxidative stress [CITATION_1] . Moreover, peak troponin I values in patients with STEMI treated with primary angioplasty are related to the presence of endothelial dysfunction [CITATION_2] . Plasma peak troponin I concentration is a valid surrogate measure of infarct size and associated with increased aortic atherosclerotic inflammation and early adverse events. Immediate and successful reperfusion for STEMI results in decreased myocardial injury, which confers greater reduction in the risk of early recurrent events.",
